<br>
A weapon is fairly easy to find wherever your at- a rock for example. Anything solid that you can pick up..... a chair, a pipe/pole/broomstick, heck even the little guy whos trying to stay out of the way. Pick him up and lob him towards your attacker <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
My keychain has a little lockblade knife, and a green LED light (green is most sensitive to eyes and is useful for signalling since it can be seen far away)<br>
<br>
I always carry around a lighter (well, a lil blowtorch) even though I don't smoke. It shoots an intimidating blue flame, is windproof, and if I light your ass on fire, it's going to do alot more damage then a lil knife hitting me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I also carry another pocketknife/tool that I can use if I need a screwdriver, pliers, etc.<br>
<br>
I could go get a Kel Tec P32 as it's probably one of the best compact pistols around, but I have no need for it, so no.<br>
<br>
I have a Level IIa concealable bulletresistant vest and a Marine Flack Jacket. Those are useful for some things (I wear the bullet resistant vest whenever I'm at the range shooting my rifle).  The Flack Jacket is useful b/c in case of heavy weather  (tornado warnings, things like that) the flack jacket will protect you from splinters, broken glass, etc. And even if nothing happens, it's comfy to have that protected feeling <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I don't really carry any weapons for self defense, most of the items I carry are more tools than weapons, although they could be used either way.<br>
<br>
The biggest thing is training/practice. Buying a pistol is, in 90% of cases, going to cause more harm than good, which is why I don't have one, even though I like them. If your situation does require a pistol for self defense, train with it, buy one your comfortable with, and shoot at least 100 rounds a week at first, then at least that every  month afterwards. If your not willing to spend the time and money for ammo for practice, don't buy the weapon. Same with throwing knives. I've seen several people here mention them- how many of you go out every day and practice? It takes more effort to learn that then it does to learn a pistol. Thats real art there-<br>
<br>
And another factor you must consider- (the following is just my opinion)<br>
A weapon is not an intimidation tool. It's a killing tool. You don't draw the weapon, knife, gun or otherwise to scare them off. If they intend to take your wallet and punch you in the face, let them if thats what it takes. Only if you are going to DIE should you draw your weapon. Otherwise you'll just get into more trouble. A self defense tool is a tool of last resort, not first.<br>
Do not, and I repeat for emphasis, do not even draw the weapon unless you are _going_ to use it. Not &quot;might have to use it&quot;, not &quot;use it to scare them off but don't intend to hurt them&quot;. Do not draw your weapon at all, keep it hidden away, unless you have to use it. Even if that means getting beat up-<br>
 If you have to draw your weapon, the steps should be as follows. 1) draw it quickly, 2) use it quickly. Don't give them warning. Don't try to intimidate them, and give them one last chance to go away. Just kill them. Immediately. If it's a knife shove and twist. If it's a gun, shoot for center mass until their body stops moving. Shoot them again when on the ground. If you are not prepared to do that, if you can't bring it to yourself to end another life, DO NOT CARRY A WEAPON. It will only get you into trouble.<br>
<br>
And that is why I do not carry a gun, even if my uncle can give me lessons for free- because I believe, even though I'm a military brat, will probably join the military, and like firearms (not in the redneck/love kind of way), I won't carry a firearm unless the situation gets to the point where my life, not my wallet, not my pride, but my life is under constant threat. Notice the constant part- that means if someone is out to get me with the intent to kill me. Not &quot;In case someone tries to mug me&quot; or similar. I don't carry around a self defense weapon &quot;in case something happens&quot; like a random mugging or a punk thats trying to beat you up after school. The only reason I'd carry one around (as a civilian) is if someone is out to kill me- and usually I'll have some kind of warning that this is going to happen, it won't be a random attack like a mugger that happens without warning.<br>
<br>
Just my $.02 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href=http://pub92.ezboard.com/bmilitaryandpolitics>Visit my Military, History, and Politics BBS</a>

